de.payleven.inappsdk.listeners

Interface RegistrationListener


  • public interface RegistrationListener
    Listener that reaction on registration result, returning either an instance of the PaylevenInAppClient in case the registration is successful or a Throwable in case the registration fails

      • onRegistrationFailed

        void onRegistrationFailed(Throwable throwable)
        Called when the payment instrument disabling failed
        Parameters:
        throwable - the error that caused the disabling failure For more details on the reason of the failure check for the instance of the Throwable. If the Throwable is a CallbackError the error code and the message encapsulated can give more insight.

        Possible instances are:

        NetworkError - in case the error was caused by a network error
